<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Smoot-Hawley Tariff Act of 1930:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Reduced international trade barriers</option>
            <option letter="b">Raised tariffs to record-high levels</option>
            <option letter="c">Created a free trade agreement with Europe</option>
            <option letter="d">Eliminated all import taxes</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Smoot-Hawley Tariff Act raised U.S. tariffs on over 20,000 imported goods to record-high levels. This protectionist measure, intended to help American businesses, actually worsened the Great Depression by prompting retaliatory tariffs from other nations and severely reducing international trade.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
